roasteries.name: Grunt palarnia kawy
roasteries.description: Jesteśmy palarnią kawy specialty z Bielska-Białej. GRUNT to dla nas powrót do korzeni. Najlepszej jakości kawa i jedzenie pod jednym dachem.

roasteries.name: HAYB Speciality Coffee
roasteries.description: Effortless speciality

roasteries.name: qb coffee roasters
roasteries.description: Jsme kávoví holisti

roasteries.name: 1000 Hills Products
roasteries.description: 1000 Hills to marka, która powstała by dostarczać kawy z Rwandy

roasteries.name: CAFFE GRANO
roasteries.description: Comprehensive service for offices, fresh coffee, professional espresso machine distribution, and service. Known for aroma and taste.

roasteries.name: BeMyBean Specialty Coffee Roasters
roasteries.description: Artisanal roastery, high-quality beans from Brazil, Ethiopia, Guatemala, Peru. Small-batch roasting for ideal balance. Online store and physical visits.

roasteries.name: Skład kawy
roasteries.description: Place where people, quality, emotions, and passion converge. Distributes throughout Poland. Offers single-origin and blends.

roasteries.name: Megan Coffee
roasteries.description: Coffees from highly controlled, certified plantations. Precise roasting for balanced flavor. Online shop and blog.

roasteries.name: HardBeans Coffee Roasters
roasteries.description: Passionate team, highest quality hand-picked beans from organic plantations. Individual roasting degrees. Continuous research for perfection.

roasteries.name: Palarnia kawy Paloma
roasteries.description: Owners learned roasting in Barcelona. Offers traditional and flavored beans. Online store for nationwide delivery.

roasteries.name: Palarnia Kawy The White Bear
roasteries.description: Passion for coffee since 2009. Offers brewing equipment, accessories, and coffee machine rentals. Double ecological packaging for freshness.

roasteries.name: Palarnia kawy „Kopernik”
roasteries.description: Family-owned, specializes in highest quality Arabica beans. Unique taste and aroma. Online store. Focus on beautiful custom packaging.

roasteries.name: Planeta Kawy
roasteries.description: Friendly, family atmosphere, expert advice. Guests can compose their own blends and design custom packaging. Cyclical home delivery.

roasteries.name: Zacisze Anioła
roasteries.description: Small cafe-roastery serving artisanal coffee. Wide selection of cakes, desserts, teas, ice creams. Small shop with freshly roasted specialty and premium beans.

roasteries.name: Momento Coffee
roasteries.description: Run by two young individuals for many years. Known for fresh beans from around the world. Online sales and cozy cafe.

roasteries.name: Coffeelab
roasteries.description: Established 2012, changed name in 2013. Uses Giesen roasters. Focus on quality and customer satisfaction.

roasteries.name: Coffee Collective Godthåbsvej
roasteries.description: A pioneering coffee roastery founded in 2007 by a group of passionate coffee professionals. They focus on direct trade, sourcing high-quality green beans directly from farmers, ensuring traceability and fair prices. They roast for clarity and complexity, offering a unique coffee experience.

roasteries.name: Java Coffee Roasters
roasteries.description: Specializes in 100% Arabica, ethically sourced since 2001. Uses Loring and Diedrich kilns. Offers diverse sensory profiles. Plants a tree for every kg sold.

roasteries.name: The Barn Coffee Roasters
roasteries.description: Leading European roaster since 2010. Focus on continuous improvement, showcasing specific flavor profiles and farms. No blends.

roasteries.name: Tim Wendelboe
roasteries.description: Offers coffee tasting and roastery tours. Features single-origin coffees. Provides various coffee subscription plans. Focus on quality and highlighting natural flavors.

roasteries.name: Drop Coffee Roasters
roasteries.description: Micro-roastery dedicated to tasty and sustainably produced coffee. Visits all producers. Focus on sweetness and vibrancy, no ashy roast flavors. Organic certified.

roasteries.name: Square Mile Coffee Roasters
roasteries.address: Unit 13, Uplands Business Park, Blackhorse Lane, London E17 5QJ
roasteries.description: Sells coffee, coffee equipment, and related products. Offers coffee subscriptions, hosts events like roastery tours and tastings, and provides wholesale options.

roasteries.name: Five Elephant
roasteries.description: Founded in 2010, dedicated to highest standards in specialty coffee. Focus on sustainable sourcing, ethical practices, and meticulous roasting. Collaborates with producers committed to environmental regeneration.

roasteries.name: Nomad Coffee
roasteries.description: Concept originated in London market, transformed into roastery in Barcelona. Runs three branches, roasts and sells coffee. Offers specialty coffee reflecting modern trends and seasonal harvests.

coffees.name: Kolumbia „Juicy Grape” Brayan Alvear Las Palmas
Blue Espresso Blend
coffees.description: Jeden z najsłodszych blendów HAYB, stworzony z myślą o miłośnikach słodyczy w kawie. Idealnie sprawdzi się do parzenia espresso w domu i kawiarni. Jest słodki, gładki i przyjemny, ale dodatek ziaren z Etiopii sprawia, że każdy łyk jest bardziej interesujący i odkrywczy.

coffees.name: Costa Rica Hacienda Sonora SL28 FILTR
coffees.description: Początkowy, soczysty łyk kawy z Kostaryki to obfitość suszonych owoców, jagód i innych soczystych nut z grupy jagodowej. Ta owocowa mieszanka to efekt zastosowania kenijskiej odmiany SL28 i metody obróbki naturalnej. Właścicielom farmy, Alberto i Diego (ojciec i syn), udało się połączyć kenijską odmianę ze swoją tradycyjną metodą obróbki naturalnej, tworząc harmonijny i czysty profil.

coffees.name: Kawa MUHABURA One & Only Filter – Arabika Specialty Competition do alternatyw
coffees.description: Czarna perła wśród kaw, czyli wyjątkowy mikrolot z Rwandy w klasyfikacji Competition. Partia, którą mamy teraz to kawa z MAHEMBE Coffee Company, która zajęła 16 miejsce na konkursie Cup of Excellence Rwanda 2024. W zaparzeniu intensywnie kwiatowa, na początku malina i trawa cytrynowa, następnie nuty brzoskwini. W miarę stygnięcia pojawia się soczyste zielone jabłko. To, co wyróżnia MUHABURA One & Only, to nietypowa, jak na kawy z Rwandy, metoda obróbki: ziarna w skórce i miąższu, poddane są suchej fermentacji.

coffees.name: Kawa MUHABURA FUNKY Espresso – Arabika Specialty Anaerobic do ekspresu i kawiarki
coffees.description: Zapewniamy, że ta kawa to eksplozja soczystych nut owoców tropikalnych! Smak jest świeży i aksamitny, a cały efekt to podróż na wakacje. W smaku wyczuwalna jest burza owoców tropikalnych i jagodowych. Słodka kwasowość, średnie body i długi i przyjemny posmak melasy.

coffees.name: Etiopia Sebseb Aba Mecha – kawa specialty CAFFE GRANO
coffees.description: Etiopia Sebseb Aba Mecha to kwintesencja kaw z tego regionu, ceniona za odporność w uprawie oraz złożoność profilu sensorycznego. W smaku to dominująca czarna herbata, owoce cytrusowe i nuty kwiatowe. Kawa ta charakteryzuje się floralnym aromatem, a smak opiera się na herbacie earl grey, która trwa również, gdy napar ostygnie. Cytrusowa kwasowość, w szczególności limonki, równoważona jest słodyczą podobną do cascary. W tle wyczuwalne są subtelne nuty wiśni i rabarbaru. W miarę stygnięcia naparu bergamotka staje się bardziej wyczuwalna, tworząc elegancką kompozycję smakową. Posmak jest wyraźnie herbaciany, a na zimno lekko kremowy.

coffees.name: Kostaryka La Guaca – kawa warszawskich eliminacji Mistrzostw Polski AEROPRESS
coffees.region: San Jose Province, Brunca region, Chirripo
coffees.description: Kawa z Kostaryki La Guaca to kawa, która brała udział w warszawskich eliminacjach Mistrzostw Polski AEROPRESS. Profil sensoryczny: banan, wino rosé, brązowy cukier.

coffees.name: Boogie Bean
coffees.description: Boogie Bean to bestsellerowe espresso z ogromem możliwości parzenia. Może być bardzo słodkie z średnią goryczką lub słodko-kwaśno-owocowe z delikatną goryczką. Jest to kawa bardzo wyrozumiała i przyjemna. Po prostu – łatwa w zaparzaniu, przyjemna w piciu. Klasyczna Brazylia charakteryzująca się umiarkowaną kwasowością, delikatną goryczką i słodyczą.

coffees.name: Ethiopia Mate Matiwos
coffees.description: Etiopia Mate Matiwos to naturalnie przetwarzana kawa o wyjątkowym profilu smakowym, pochodząca z regionu Sidamo w Etiopii. Rośnie na wysokości 2300 metrów nad poziomem morza, co przyczynia się do jej głębokiej i złożonej struktury. Chłodniejszy klimat na tej wysokości pozwala ziarnom dojrzewać powoli, rozwijając wyjątkowy smak.

coffees.name: Brazil Santos
coffees.description: Kawa Brazylia Santos to delikatna i aromatyczna kawa o niskiej kwasowości i goryczce. Idealna dla tych, którzy cenią sobie wyważone smaki i aromaty w kawie.

coffees.name: Arabica coffee - Brazil Santos
coffees.description: Ziarna kawy Arabica Brazil Santos są bardzo aromatyczne i pozbawione nadmiernej kwasowości i goryczki. Szczególnie pasują koneserom kaw jednorodnych, którzy poszukują zrównoważonych smaków. Kawa nosi nazwę „Santos” od brazylijskiego portu, który stał się sławny, kiedy Brazylia stała się światowym potentatem w produkcji kawy.

coffees.name: Arabica coffee - Ethiopia Sidamo
coffees.description: Etiopia Sidamo to arabika pochodząca z Afryki Północno-Wschodniej. Uważana jest za miejsce, z którego pochodzi drzewo kawowe. Kawa uprawiana jest w regionie Sidamo, na południe od Addis Abeby, na wysokości od 1200 do 1900 metrów nad poziomem morza. Surowe ziarno ma intensywny zielony kolor, jest bardziej okrągłe niż płaskie i niewielkich rozmiarów. Kawa ta uprawiana jest w „ogrodach kawowych” wśród bananowców, tytoniu, przypraw i herbaty, co nadaje jej niezwykły i niepowtarzalny aromat.

coffees.name: Kicker Espresso, Brazylia & Indie Blend
coffees.description: Kicker Espresso to kawa blend z 80% arabiki i 20% robusty. W smaku dominują nuty ciemnej czekolady, orzechów włoskich i karmelu. Kwasowość jest niska. W kawach mlecznych przyjemne połączenie kakao i orzechów z łagodnym karmelowym finiszem. W czarnej kawie wyraźne nuty gorzkiej czekolady i orzechów.

coffees.name: Dominikana Finca La Colonia
coffees.description: Dominikana Finca La Colonia 250g to kawa dla miłośników głębokich, zdecydowanych smaków, dalekich od lekkości czy owocowej kwasowości. Skórzane, tytoniowe, kakaowe, intensywne, gęste i charakterne, ale harmonijne. Zamiast owoców i cytrusów oferuje aksamitne body i długi, suchy finisz.

coffees.name: Boliwia Finca Genesis Marco Cabera Natural
coffees.description: Boliwia Finca Genesis Marco Cabera Natural 250g to wyjątkowa kawa, pochodząca z regionu Taipiplaya w La Paz. Jest to blend z 15 rodzin należących do kooperatywy ASOCAFE, która zrzesza 280 członków. Kawa dedykowana jest do metod przelewowych. Naturalna obróbka podkreśla jej słodycz, dominujące nuty to dojrzałe wiśnie, jeżyny i miękka wanilia, tworząc intensywny, soczysty profil. Smak jest gładki, przypominający słodkie cukierki, z interesującymi słodko-kwaśnymi akcentami w posmaku, podobnymi do kwaśnych żelków.

coffees.name: RADIOPHARE
coffees.description: New seasonal flavor: RADIOPHARE, with notes of passion fruit and citrus.

coffees.name: A DROP OF SCIENCE
coffees.description: New release: A DROP OF SCIENCE (chocolate, dried apricot from Brazil).

coffees.name: Carmelita Washed Java
coffees.description: This coffee is currently sold out.

coffees.name: Nano Challa, Washed Heirloom
coffees.description: This coffee is currently sold out. Organic certified.

coffees.name: EL SALVADOR La Cancha Natural – Filter

shops.name: Serwis Cafe & Pub
shops.description: Cycling-themed Serwis Cafe & Pub in Katowice serves specialty coffee alongside craft beer and Neapolitan pizza. Decorated with bicycle memorabilia, it hosts biweekly coffee-tasting sessions for guests.

shops.name: Coffee Synergia
shops.description: Coffee Synergia epitomizes Katowice’s third-wave scene with its rustic industrial interior and an array of brewing methods (espresso, Chemex, drip, Aeropress). It offers sweet and savory treats, including hearty vegan/gluten-free brunch options, in a relaxed atmosphere.

shops.name: Proper Coffee
shops.description: Proper Coffee in Katowice is a small specialty cafe roasting its own beans. It offers a range of espresso and manual brews with beans from carefully selected origins. Customers praise the expertly prepared drinks and cozy atmosphere.

shops.name: Kafej
shops.description: Kafej is a pastel-hued cafe and brunch spot at a busy Katowice intersection. It’s known as one of the city’s best brunch places, serving fresh bagels, omelets, pancakes and burritos, with seating on a leafy patio.

shops.name: Black Woolf Coffee & Books
shops.description: Black Woolf Coffee & Books blends specialty coffee with a vibrant cultural hub. With a bright pink espresso machine and eclectic décor, it serves excellent coffee and hosts events like art exhibitions and author talks.

shops.name: Bezcukru
shops.description: Bezcukru is a stylish independent cafe in Katowice known for its high-quality coffee, teas, and sweet treats. The modern elegant interior and wide variety of specialty drinks make it a popular spot among locals.

shops.name: Ministerstwo Kawy
shops.description: Ministerstwo Kawy (Warsaw) is a beloved specialty coffee spot with a minimalist, sunlit interior. It serves Koppi espresso roasts and rotating filter coffees, along with pastries and cakes. Reviewers praise its cozy atmosphere and consistently excellent coffee.

shops.name: Filtry Cafe
shops.description: Filtry Cafe is known as Warsaw’s first specialty coffee shop. This cozy neighborhood cafe offers espresso, flat white and manual brew methods like Chemex and siphon using beans from Swedish Drop Coffee and local roasters. Customers highlight its great atmosphere, friendly service, and homemade cakes.

shops.name: Forum Coffee
shops.description: Forum Coffee (Warsaw) is run by award-winning baristas (Polish Aeropress and Brewers Cup champions). The cafe is known for its stylish interior and a resident dog named Apollo. It serves seasonal beans, often prepared via AeroPress, and exquisite espresso drinks.

shops.name: OTO Coffee Bar
shops.description: OTO Coffee Bar in Wrocław is praised for serving some of the city’s best specialty coffee. It offers decaf and oat milk options, and reviewers note the beautifully crafted flat whites. The cafe’s cozy atmosphere, vinyl music selection, and delicious cakes add to its charm.

shops.name: Rozrusznik
shops.description: Rozrusznik (Wrocław) is the city’s oldest specialty coffee shop (opened 2011) in a renovated workshop. It features a youthful interior with sofas and vinyl records. Owned by a former Bristol resident, the cafe emphasizes community and quality coffee sourced via direct trade.

shops.name: String Taste
shops.description: String Taste combines specialty coffee with a passion for guitars. This unique Kraków cafe displays high-end guitars on the walls and often hosts live jam sessions. Patrons can enjoy expertly brewed coffee while surrounded by musical instruments.

shops.name: FABLE Cafe
shops.description: FABLE Cafe is a boutique specialty coffee spot in Kraków known for its relaxed vibe and all-day breakfast menu. It serves specialty espresso and pour-over coffees along with homemade pastries and sandwiches. The modern cozy interior makes it a popular local hangout.

shops.name: Prawdziwa Kawa
shops.description: Prawdziwa Kawa is a specialty coffee bar in Warsaw focusing on precision brewing. The minimalist cafe offers espresso and filter coffees from rotating roasters, and has a reputation for technically excellent drinks and friendly service.

shops.name: Drukarnia Cafe
shops.description: Drukarnia Cafe (Gdańsk) is a specialty coffee cafe in the city’s historic center. It offers high-quality espresso and filter coffees, plus fresh pastries and lunch dishes. The cozy interior blends modern design with industrial touches, making it a top pick among locals.

shops.name: Cafe Borówka
shops.description: Cafe Borówka is a specialty coffee and dessert shop in Wrocław. With a cozy Scandi-style interior, it offers a range of single-origin beans brewed as espresso and pour-overs. The cafe is praised for its homemade cakes and sandwiches that pair well with the excellent coffee.

shops.name: Cafe Rozliczenie
shops.description: Cafe Rozliczenie (Kraków) is a specialty cafe (its name means "the tab") focusing on high-end espresso and pour-over coffee. It’s located on a historic street and features unique brewing equipment. Visitors enjoy the expert coffee preparation and modern, comfortable setting.

shops.name: Fuglen
shops.description: Fuglen (Tokyo) is a small specialty coffee shop with a vintage Scandinavian vibe. It serves expertly roasted espresso and pour-overs by day, and turns into a cocktail bar by night. Beans are sourced from top micro-roasters, and the minimalist interior is a popular photo spot.

shops.name: Single O
shops.description: Single O is an independent specialty coffee roaster and cafe in Sydney known for its ethically sourced beans and modern cafe space. It offers a full menu of coffee beverages, including unique filter brews and signature espresso drinks, plus brunch items. The roastery's reputation attracts coffee enthusiasts globally.

shops.name: The Barn Coffee Roasters
shops.description: The Barn is a renowned specialty coffee roaster and cafe in Berlin. Housed in a minimalist space, it focuses on single-origin beans and precise brewing methods. It is famous for its strong, balanced espresso and regularly draws coffee enthusiasts from around the world.

shops.name: Five Elephant
shops.description: Five Elephant in Berlin is known for its specialty coffee and signature cheesecake. It’s a small roastery-cafe serving carefully prepared espresso and filter coffees. Visitors often note the relaxed atmosphere and high-quality beans sourced with an emphasis on sustainability.

shops.name: Coffee Collective
shops.description: Coffee Collective is an award-winning Danish specialty coffee roaster with multiple cafes in Copenhagen. It focuses on traceability and direct-trade beans. Their cafes are known for bright-filter coffee and lively atmosphere, often serving as community hubs for coffee enthusiasts.

shops.name: Democratic Coffee
shops.description: Democratic Coffee in Copenhagen is a tiny specialty cafe famous for its expertly made espresso and outstanding croissants. The shop focuses on top-quality beans and a simple menu. Despite its small size, it has earned a cult following among coffee lovers.

shops.name: Drop Coffee Roasters
shops.description: Drop Coffee Roasters in Stockholm is a specialty cafe and roastery led by World Barista Champion Martin Ingvarsson. It offers a range of single-origin filter coffees and espresso drinks. The bright, minimalist cafe and its award-winning baristas make it a pilgrimage site for coffee fans.

shops.name: Tim Wendelboe
shops.description: Tim Wendelboe is a world-champion barista’s cafe and roastery in Oslo. It is famous for its precision and quality, offering meticulously brewed coffee and espresso from its own roasted beans. The bright, Scandinavian-style cafe also sells beans and equipment to replicate their brew methods at home.

shops.name: Caffè Propaganda
shops.description: Caffè Propaganda is a specialty coffee cafe in Rome run by a renowned coffee roaster. It offers expertly brewed espresso and filter coffee in a stylish, modern setting. The menu includes Italian and international pastries, and the cafe is beloved for its consistency and quality.

shops.name: Pavè Caffè
shops.description: Pavè Caffè is the coffee branch of the famous Milanese bakery Pavè. It serves specialty espresso and espresso-based drinks using quality beans, as well as its signature pastries and sandwiches. The cafe’s hip, modern decor and delicious offerings make it a neighborhood favorite.

shops.name: Satan's Coffee Corner
shops.description: Satan's Coffee Corner is a popular Barcelona specialty cafe known for its hipster vibe and quality brews. It offers a concise menu of espresso and filter coffee made from top specialty beans, as well as craft beer and natural wine. The minimalist interior and friendly staff attract both locals and tourists.

shops.name: Blue Bottle Coffee
shops.description: Blue Bottle Coffee is a now-international specialty coffee roaster with origins in Oakland. Its NYC locations serve meticulously prepared espresso and pour-over coffee from seasonal beans. It is known for strict freshness (beans used within 48 hours of roasting) and has a sleek modern cafe design.

shops.name: Sightglass Coffee
shops.description: Sightglass Coffee is an artisanal coffee roaster and cafe in San Francisco. Housed in a converted warehouse, it offers high-quality espresso and filter coffees roasted on-site. The spacious industrial interior and knowledgeable staff make it a standout destination for specialty coffee.

shops.name: Stumptown Coffee Roasters
shops.description: Stumptown Coffee Roasters is one of America’s pioneering specialty coffee chains, founded in Portland. It sources high-quality beans and roasts them in-house. The cafes serve a range of espresso and cold brew drinks; the baristas are known for skilled espresso-making and latte art.

shops.name: Truth Coffee
shops.description: Truth Coffee in Cape Town is known for its steampunk-inspired décor and exceptional coffee. The cafe roasts its own beans and offers a wide range of espresso and filter coffees. It has frequently been rated among the best coffee shops in Africa for its quality and ambiance.

shops.name: Drop Coffee Roasters
shops.description: Drop Coffee Roasters (LA) is a specialty cafe known for high-end single-origin coffees. It offers meticulously brewed pour-overs and espresso in a sleek interior. The staff is passionate about brewing technique, making it a destination for coffee aficionados on the West Coast.

shops.name: Revolver
shops.description: Revolver in Vancouver focuses on single-origin specialty coffee. The baristas rotate a selection of the world’s top beans and brew them to order. It has a minimalist interior and a reputation for exceptional pour-over coffee, making it a must-visit in Vancouver’s coffee scene.

shops.name: Cafe Grumpy
shops.description: Cafe Grumpy is a Brooklyn specialty coffee shop and roaster with multiple NYC locations. It serves a variety of in-house roasted espresso and filter coffees. Known for its unpretentious attitude and excellent coffee, it was also featured on TV for its role in coffee culture.

shops.name: La Cabra Coffee
shops.description: La Cabra is a beloved Danish roastery and cafe with locations in Aarhus and Copenhagen. It offers exceptional espresso and carefully brewed filter coffees. The design is bright and airy, and the cafe often sells its roasted beans and merchandise alongside its handcrafted beverages.

shops.name: Drop Coffee Roasters
shops.description: Drop Coffee Roasters in Copenhagen (not to be confused with Stockholm’s Drop) is an independent cafe known for innovative blends and single origins. It offers strong espresso and creative filter drinks in a cozy setting, often complementing coffee with freshly baked pastries.

shops.name: Monmouth Coffee Company
shops.description: Monmouth Coffee Company is a historic London roaster and cafe that helped pioneer the UK’s specialty coffee scene. It sources and roasts ethically traded beans from around the world. The original cafes in Covent Garden and Borough Market serve expertly pulled espresso and pour-over coffee, attracting locals and tourists alike.

shops.name: Coffee Project NY
shops.description: Coffee Project NY in Manhattan is a specialty cafe known for using seasonal single-origin beans. The baristas hand-brew filter coffees and serve espresso in their modern, minimalist cafes. It’s known for its nitro cold brew on tap and innovative flavored lattes.

shops.name: Tim Wendelboe (Tokyo)
shops.description: Tim Wendelboe’s Tokyo branch brings the Norwegian champion barista’s vision to Japan. It serves the same award-winning espresso and filter coffees in a sleek urban setting. The cafe emphasizes simplicity and quality, making it a popular stop for Tokyo coffee aficionados.

shops.name: The Coffee Academics
shops.description: The Coffee Academics is a leading specialty coffee chain in Hong Kong. It serves a broad range of coffee drinks from local and international roasters, in addition to offering a curated tea selection. Its flagship locations feature stylish interiors and an educational approach to coffee culture.

shops.name: 49th Parallel Coffee Roasters
shops.description: 49th Parallel is a specialty roaster and cafe in Vancouver. It offers its own roasted beans brewed as espresso and pour-over coffee. The spacious cafe has a bright, welcoming atmosphere, and is known for its delicious Matcha lattes as well as coffee.

shops.name: Coffee Collective (Aarhus)
shops.description: Coffee Collective’s Aarhus location (Codd) is a lively spot offering their own roasted coffee. It has a bright interior and an attached specialty tea bar. The cafe emphasizes transparency, often publishing harvest reports for its beans and hosting classes on brewing and tasting.

shops.name: Pilgrm (Copenhagen)
shops.description: Pilgrm is a Copenhagen specialty cafe sourcing beans from the Coffee Collective. It focuses on hand-brewed filter coffee and quality espresso. The cafe’s interior features marble counters and vintage decor, providing a cozy environment to enjoy their carefully made drinks.

shops.name: La Colombe Torrefaction
shops.description: La Colombe Torrefaction is the Philadelphia outpost of the well-known specialty coffee roaster. It offers specialty espresso and draft lattes made with La Colombe’s own beans. The cafe has a bright, modern design and also sells La Colombe merchandise, making it a destination for serious coffee fans.

shops.name: Toby’s Estate Coffee Roasters
shops.description: Toby’s Estate is an Australian specialty coffee roaster and cafe chain. In Sydney, its cafes serve direct-trade beans roasted on-site. The Ultimo cafe has a large, industrial-chic space, and the baristas are skilled at brewing pour-overs and espresso drinks that highlight the coffee’s origin flavors.

shops.name: Workshop Coffee
shops.description: Workshop Coffee is a London-based specialty coffee roaster with multiple cafes. It serves carefully sourced beans brewed as espresso and filter coffee. Known for precision and quality, each latte is prepared to highlight the tasting notes of the single-origin beans.

shops.name: Intelligentsia Coffee
shops.description: Intelligentsia Coffee is a pioneering Chicago specialty coffee roaster with several cafes. It is known for sourcing high-quality beans and an emphasis on direct trade. The coffee is expertly roasted and brewed, and the cafes offer a range of espresso and filter drinks in a bright, modern setting.

shops.name: Cafe de los Deseos
shops.description: Cafe de los Deseos is a specialty coffee shop in Mexico City’s Roma neighborhood. It offers expertly brewed Mexican single-origin coffees and espresso drinks. The interior is colorful and creative, reflecting the local art scene, and the staff often shares stories about the coffee origins.

shops.name: Catación
shops.description: Catación in Bogotá is a specialty coffee shop run by lovers of coffee and design. It sources Colombian single-origin beans and brews them with care. The chic cafe also sells bags of its roasted coffee, and the owners often host tasting events, creating a dedicated community of coffee aficionados.

reviews.review: Kolumbia „Juicy Grape” to prawdziwa eksplozja smaków! Niesamowite połączenie słodyczy i owocowej kwasowości.
Bardzo ciekawa kawa, choć dla mnie trochę za bardzo owocowa. Niemniej, warto spróbować!
